HEADWORD: Micronesian
<hw>Mi"cro*ne"sian</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Micronesia</ets>, fr. Gr. <grk>mikro`s</grk> small +
<grk>nh^sos</grk> an island.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Micronesia,
a collective designation of the islands in the western part of the
Pacific Ocean, embracing the Marshall and Gilbert groups, the Ladrones,
the Carolines, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

